  "modeledFrom": [
    "00:00 Reference silhouette: The finished model is a seated teddy-bear doll with a round head, oval body, protruding muzzle, side ears, small black eyes, arms, feet, and BEAR DOLL text.",
    "01:00 Head and body: Block the main silhouette with large rounded spheres before adding details.",
    "02:00 Muzzle and face base: Add a shallow oval muzzle on the front of the head, then keep later eye and nose landmarks aligned to it.",
    "04:30 Eyes, nose, ears: Mirror small black eyes and a nose across the centerline; add round side ears with lighter inner pads.",
    "06:00 Body assembly: Place the body under the head with a pale oval belly patch, preserving the plush doll proportions.",
    "08:30 Arms: Use mirrored tapered oval arms that hang down the sides of the body.",
    "10:00 Legs and feet: Use forward-facing oval feet and small sole pads so the doll reads as seated.",
    "12:00 Final title: Add BEAR DOLL text as flat yellow geometry on the workplane next to the doll."
  ],
